def: Distance of any heavenly body south of the equator; southdeclination; south latitude.

Astonishing; wonderful; amazing; especially, astonishing inmagnitude or elevation; as, a stupendous pile. "A stupendous sum."Macaulay.All are but parts of one stupendous whole. Pope.-- Stu*pen"dous*ly, adv.-- Stu*pen"dous*ness, n.
Having elongated hairs, feathers, or bristles on the cheeks.The whiskered vermin race. Grainger.

An advocate of confederation; specifically (Amer. Hist.), afriend of the Constitution of the United States at its formation andadoption; a member of the political party which favored theadministration of president Washington.
To wish mutually in regarded to each other. [Obs.] Donne.
A suborder of Neuroptera usually having the wings covered withminute hairs. It comprises the caddice flies, and is considered bysome to be a distinct order.
Pertaining to the science or doctrine of refracted sounds.
To bend; as, to flex the arm.
The berry of the dogwood; -- called also dogcherry. Dr. Prior.Dogberry tree (Bot.), the dogwood.
To put to inconvenience; to incommode. [R.] Bp. Warburton.
